</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A3F54D4E650C047F2B286D41FD71DD0E" authority="Richardson, 2013" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="2013" box="[313,727,290,316]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Frewena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650C047F2B286D41FDADDD0E" box="[313,523,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="262">Frewena maculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="00644B3C650C047F28036D40FD71DD0E" author="Richardson, B. J." box="[530,727,290,316]" pageId="13" pageNumber="262" pagination="460 - 474" refId="ref13554" refString="Richardson, B. J. (2013) New unidentate jumping spider genera (Araneae: Salticidae) from Australia. Zootaxa, 3716 (3), 460 - 474. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3716.3.8" type="journal article" year="2013">Richardson, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="644A36CD650C047F2AD66D27FDC1DDC2" blockId="13.[151,1437,289,496]" pageId="13" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650C047F2AD66D27FE0FDD6D" bold="true" box="[199,425,325,351]" pageId="13" pageNumber="262">Revised Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This Australian genus of very small unidentate spiders can be distinguished from other euophryine genera by the shape of the spermatheca. This is subdivided into two compartments placed one on top of the other and with a well-formed long narrow diverticulum off the ventral compartment. The paired fossae are separated by a distinct septa and include two S-shaped guides. The male has a long embolus forming an anticlockwise spiral. L3 is the longest leg in both sexes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="308A6645650C047F2A866BFDFC57DBEE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592720" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6592720" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592720/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="262" startId="13.[151,264,1951,1975]" targetBox="[158,1432,523,1907]" targetPageId="13">
