<subSubSection id="2CEF6546650F047C2AD66CF5FD4CDD73" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="644A36CD650F047C2AD66CF5FD4CDD73" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,321]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C2AD66CF5FE9DDC83" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A3F54D4E650F047C2B506CF5FE02DC82" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="2013" box="[321,420,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Frewena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C2B506CF5FE02DC82" box="[321,420,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Frewena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of material from the 
<collectingRegion id="A631F82F650F047C29AA6CF5FB2CDC83" box="[955,1162,151,177]" country="Australia" name="Northern Territory" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Northern Territory</collectingRegion>
.A second species of this genus has now been collected from central 
<collectingRegion id="A631F82F650F047C286E6CD9FCA5DCE7" box="[639,771,187,213]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="FCCE2A48650F047C29056CD9FCCEDCE4" box="[788,872,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–60" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[158,1432,523,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-108@13.[151,1436,520,1928]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 53–60. Frewena terraregina n. sp. Holotype (42 001432), (male; 53 dorsal, 54 ventral, 55 lateral, 56 anterior 57 anterior palp, 58 ventral palp, 59 posterior palp); 60 distribution map. Scale: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592720" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592720/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). L 
<quantity id="A30D9B28650F047C299E6CD9FC1FDCE7" box="[911,953,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
both species is much longer than the other legs but without strong markings or fringes, raising the possibility they are related to the 
<taxonomicName id="A3F54D4E650F047C2E8C6CBDFA3ADCCB" authority="Karsch, 1878" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1878" box="[1181,1436,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C2E8C6CBDFB5ADCCA" box="[1181,1276,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Maratus</emphasis>
Karsch, 1878
</taxonomicName>
group amongst the Australian euophryines (
<bibRefCitation id="00644B3C650F047C286D6D61FCE6DD2F" author="Otto, J. C. &amp; Hill, D. E." box="[636,832,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref13470" refString="Otto, J. C. &amp; Hill, D. E. (2021) Catalogue of the Australian peacock spiders (Araneae: Salticidae: Euophryini: Maratus), version 4. Peckhamia, 148 (4), 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="2021">Otto &amp; Hill 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Alternatively, 
<taxonomicName id="A3F54D4E650F047C29E16D61FBF5DD2E" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="2013" box="[1008,1107,259,284]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Frewena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C29E16D61FBF5DD2E" box="[1008,1107,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Frewena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has independently developed the use of L 
<quantity id="A30D9B28650F047C2B0F6D45FEE1DD73" box="[286,327,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
mating rituals in parallel to 
<taxonomicName id="A3F54D4E650F047C28956D45FD45DD72" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1878" box="[644,739,295,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5681EADF650F047C28956D45FD45DD72" box="[644,739,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="263">Maratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
